summary: Completed comprehensive testing of Journeyman dating app MVP. Backend APIs mostly functional (14/16 tests passed), frontend UI working well with successful user registration and onboarding flow. Found 2 critical backend issues that need fixing.

critical_bugs.issue: Returns 500 Internal Server Error due to MongoDB ObjectId serialization error
critical_bugs.error_details: ValueError: [TypeError("'ObjectId' object is not iterable"), TypeError('vars() argument must have __dict__ attribute')]
critical_bugs.recommended_fix: Replace MongoDB ObjectId usage with UUID strings for JSON serialization compatibility

minor_issues.issue: Match action fails when no users available for matching
minor_issues.impact: Expected behavior in fresh system, but should handle gracefully

passed_tests: Landing page loads with correct blue/gold branding
Signup page UI and form submission
Complete onboarding flow with profession selection
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix MongoDB ObjectId serialization issue in schedule creation endpoint (/api/schedules). Replace ObjectId usage with UUID strings to ensure JSON serialization compatibility. This is blocking the travel schedules feature completely.

success_percentage.frontend: 95% (UI flows working, minor auth session handling expected)
